&lt;h1&gt;Bank Nurse, Band 5 (Inpatients)&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you take pride in what you do? Delivering safe, compassionate care, resulting in a high-quality patient experience? If so Oxleas NHS Foundation Trust are looking for people like you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust has a high number of staff, who have worked for us for many years, with a high standard of clinical expertise. Our staff are passionate about the care they provide and this is reflected in the feedback we receive from our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are always on the lookout for people with the same values as us and who believe in putting their patients first and delivering an exceptional level of patient care. We have opportunities for people to work for our inpatient areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joining as one of our bank workers is a great way to experience this for yourselves and meeting the passionate people who work for the Trust going the extra mile every day for our patients. Sound exciting? What are you waiting for - apply now.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as a bank member of staff means greater flexibility for you. We can offer a range of shifts to fit around you – be that on an ad-hoc basis or more regular lines of work on a rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that we require a minimum of six months post qualification experience to join our Bank.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you feel that you are dynamic, enthusiastic, an excellent communicator and know/feel that you can meet our expectations - you will certainly be in for an exciting and rewarding time at Oxleas as we do more than empower nurses, we inspire them!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proposed Interview Date: Week Commencing Monday 16th November*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;*Please note this may be subject to change&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For internal Staff looking to join the Bank in another role, please find further details under &#39;Joining the Staff Bank&#39; on the Trust&#39;s intranet site - The Ox.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Naidoo Armoordon, Modern Matron:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: naidoo.armoordon@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 0203 889 5176&lt;/p&gt;
